description:
The Silk Road

This is the best and most detailed research documentary on &quot;Silk Road&quot; from historic and geographic viewpionts. There are a total of 12 episodes and more than 600 minutes in total. A joint venture work between NHK and China Central TV which took 10 years and 50 million dollars to complete.

The video was shot 10-20 years ago and certainly show its age. Central Park Media did not spend any more effort to improve its quality from the previous LD. There is no chapter selection in each episode. Once start, you have to sit through the entire episode which is about 50-55 minutes long.


The Silk Road 01 Glories of Ancient Chang-An.avi
The Silk Road 02 A Thousand Kilometers Beyond The Yellow River.avi
The Silk Road 03 The Art Gallery in the Desert.avi
The Silk Road 04 The Dark Castle.avi
The Silk Road 05 In Search of the Kingdom of Lou-Lan.avi
The Silk Road 06 Across The Taklamakan Desert.avi
The Silk Road 07 Khotan-Oasis of Silk and Jade.avi
The Silk Road 08 A Heat Wave Called Turfan.avi
The Silk Road 09 Through the Tian Shan Mountains by Rail.avi
The Silk Road 10 Journey Into Music-South Through The Tian Shan Mountains.avi
The Silk Road 11 Where Horses Fly Like the Wind.avi
The Silk Road 12 Two Roads to the Pamirs.avi

